<subSubSection id="C9C6F1F7FF67CEB1FCA0F835DF5A3403" lastPageId="236" lastPageNumber="237" pageId="234" pageNumber="235" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8163A27CFF67CEB1FCA0F835DA2639C5" blockId="234.[810,1451,1929,2092]" lastBlockId="236.[136,778,1342,2093]" lastPageId="236" lastPageNumber="237" pageId="234" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF67CEB7FCA0F835D88A3BD0" bold="true" box="[863,985,2020,2046]" pageId="234" pageNumber="235">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Females of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF67CEB7FB9CF834DF903BD1" authorityName="Chamberlin" authorityYear="1917" box="[1123,1219,2021,2047]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="234" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xenus">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF67CEB7FB9CF834DF903BD1" box="[1123,1219,2021,2047]" italics="true" pageId="234" pageNumber="235">A. xenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are characterized by the following combination of characters: unilobed seminal receptacles, which are subquadrate in shape and parallel to each other; apical external edge of each receptacle longer than internal edge (
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FF61CEB1FE55FA59D970398C" box="[426,547,1416,1442]" captionStart="FIGURE 214" captionStartId="236.[136,235,1180,1204]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,189,1157]" captionTargetId="figure-360@236.[151,1435,189,1157]" captionTargetPageId="236" captionText="FIGURE 214 A. Actinopus xenus Chamberlin, 1917, holotype, female: A MCZ 03: A. Spermathecae, dorsal view. Photo: R. Saturnino." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597703/files/figure.png" pageId="236" pageNumber="237">Fig. 214 A</figureCitation>
). Smooth corrugated area on inner surface of Chelicerae less evident than in 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF61CEB1FD0DFA7CDB8D39C5" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1949" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="236" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="echinus">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF61CEB1FD0DFA7CDB8D39C5" italics="true" pageId="236" pageNumber="237">A. echinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FF61CEB1FF12FA00DA3439C5" box="[237,359,1489,1515]" captionStart="FIGURE 210" captionStartId="232.[136,235,1645,1669]" captionTargetBox="[175,1411,205,1605]" captionTargetId="figure-143@232.[151,1436,189,1621]" captionTargetPageId="232" captionText="FIGURE 210. Actinopus echinus Mello-Leit„o, 1949, female: A–F IBSP 102907: A. Abdomen, dorsal; B. Carapace, dorsal; C. Sternum, ventral; D. Cheliceral teeth, ventral; E. Rastellum, dorsal; F. Rastellum, ventral. Scales lines B–C: 0.5 mm, D: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597695/files/figure.png" pageId="236" pageNumber="237">Fig. 210 B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
